Mark Biderman



















												Mark Biderman,											


												LLB											





												Vice President, Trust and Legal, Cidel Trust Company											




														+1 416 928 4118													





														mbiderman@cidel.com													






Mark Biderman is the Vice President, Trust and Legal at Cidel. In his role as Vice President, Mark is responsible for the operations of Cidel Trust Company as well as new business initiatives. He also acts as in-house corporate counsel and taxation law specialist at Cidel. Prior to joining Cidel, Mark was a lawyer in the tax group of Goodmans LLP, a leading Canadian law firm where he advised on numerous public and private transactions for a wide range of clients. Mark has authored several tax articles with a particular focus on international taxation law. Mark is a member of the board of directors of Camp Solelim and is a member of the Law Society of Upper Canada. Mark holds a BA (Honours) from Huron University College, University of Western Ontario, and an LLB from Osgoode Hall Law School, York University.














Susan Blanchard



















												Susan Blanchard,											


												CFA											





												Portfolio Manager, Cidel Asset Management Inc.											




														+1 416 645 5235													





														sblanchard@cidel.com													






Susan is a portfolio manager specializing in small cap Canadian equities. She has over 40 years of investment industry experience, starting at AMI Partners, now part of Cidel. While managing high-net-worth clients’ portfolios, she helped develop the Growing Income strategy for individuals and charities seeking companies with growing dividends.  In 1991 she moved from the Montreal office to Toronto.  As small cap lead, Susan is a member of the Canadian equity research team.  Susan is a CFA charterholder and a graduate of the University of Waterloo.














