Amanda Lashley



















												Amanda Lashley,											


												LLB, LEC, TEP											





												Vice President, Trust Services, Cidel Bank and Trust Inc.											




														+1 246 430 5350													





														alashley@cidel.com													






Amanda’s responsibilities include managing Cidel’s trust services division and advising on aspects of law relating to trusts, wills, and estates. Prior to joining Cidel, Amanda worked with a Barbados offshore bank as the vice president of structured services, where she managed international trust and corporate relationships and worked on corporate, commercial and international business transactions. Her previous experience also includes working at Royal Bank of Canada in Barbados as a senior trust officer and PricewaterhouseCoopers in Barbados as a senior associate.
Amanda is a member of the Barbados branch of the Society of Trust and Estate Practitioners and has published articles on Trusts for the STEP Journal and is currently the Branch Chair. Amanda holds an LLB from the University of the West Indies and in 1997 was called to the bar of Barbados and Trinidad, she has an LEC from Hugh Wooding Law school, and TEP designation from the Society of Trust and Estate Practitioners.














Matt Maldoff



















												Matt Maldoff,											


												CFA											





												Assistant Vice President, Senior Analyst, Portfolio Manager, Cidel Asset Management Inc.											




														+1 416 925 7585													





														mmaldoff@cidel.com													






Matt is responsible for hedge fund portfolio allocations, portfolio risk management, on-site due diligence visits with hedge fund managers, quantitative and qualitative analysis of hedge fund managers and arbitrage strategies. He is an analyst for the Ascent Relative Value Fund, Ltd. and sits on the investment committee. Matt graduated from Richard Ivey School of Business at the University of Western Ontario in 2005 with a Bachelor of Arts in Business Administration (Honours). He is a CFA charterholder and a member of the Toronto CFA Society and the CFA Institute.














Geoff Matus



















												Geoff Matus											






												Chairman,  Cidel Bank Canada											




														+1 416 928 4110													





														gmatus@cidel.com													






Geoff is the chairman and co-founder of Cidel. He is a director of a number of other international manufacturing and financial companies, including Tricon Capital which he co-founded. He has a sustained record of volunteer work in Canada: he is an honorary director and past chair of the board of directors of the Baycrest Centre for Geriatric Care; a past member of the board of the Canadian Opera Company; the board of Mount Sinai Hospital and the board of Governing Council of the University of Toronto, where he currently chairs the Pension and Endowment Investment Advisory Committee. Geoff is a member of the board and chair of the Real Estate Committee of the MaRS Discovery District.
In 2005, Geoff was a recipient of the Jewish Federation award for outstanding service to the community. In 2010, he received the Arbor Award for outstanding service to the University of Toronto and in 2011 he was honoured as “Man of Distinction” by the Israel Cancer Research Fund. Born and raised in South Africa, Geoff graduated with Bachelor of Commerce and LLB from Wits University, and received a Law Degree from Columbia University in New York. While at Wits, Geoff was a co-founder of The Legal Resource Centre in South Africa, when he was the President of the Wits Law Students Council.














