Page Arthur B Has $409,000 Stake in DENTSPLY SIRONA Inc. (XRAY)

					Posted by Mitch Edgeman on Jul 24th, 2017 // No Comments 




Page Arthur B held its position in  DENTSPLY SIRONA Inc. (NASDAQ:XRAY) during the second quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The firm owned 6,303 shares of the medical instruments supplier’s stock at the end of the second quarter. Page Arthur B’s holdings in DENTSPLY SIRONA were worth $409,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Several other institutional investors have also bought and sold shares of the stock. BB&T Corp raised its position in  DENTSPLY SIRONA by 32.2% in the second quarter. BB&T Corp now owns 14,961 shares of the medical instruments supplier’s stock valued at $970,000 after buying an additional 3,642 shares during the last quarter.  Oakbrook Investments LLC acquired a new position in  DENTSPLY SIRONA during the second quarter valued at $671,000.  US Bancorp DE raised its position in  DENTSPLY SIRONA by 0.6% in the second quarter. US Bancorp DE now owns 28,435 shares of the medical instruments supplier’s stock valued at $1,843,000 after buying an additional 165 shares during the last quarter.  BTIM Corp. raised its position in  DENTSPLY SIRONA by 51.2% in the second quarter. BTIM Corp. now owns 690,631 shares of the medical instruments supplier’s stock valued at $44,781,000 after buying an additional 233,929 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, Aperio Group LLC raised its position in  DENTSPLY SIRONA by 10.1% in the second quarter. Aperio Group LLC now owns 108,386 shares of the medical instruments supplier’s stock valued at $7,028,000 after buying an additional 9,973 shares during the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  94.92% of the company’s stock. 


 Get DENTSPLY SIRONA Inc. alerts:



DENTSPLY SIRONA Inc. (NASDAQ XRAY) traded down 0.64% during midday trading on Monday, hitting $62.52. 449,105 shares of the stock traded hands. The stock has a market cap of $14.33 billion, a PE ratio of 40.23 and a beta of 1.27. DENTSPLY SIRONA Inc. has a 1-year low of $55.00 and a 1-year high of $65.68. The company has a 50-day moving average of $64.12 and a 200-day moving average of $61.96. 




DENTSPLY SIRONA (NASDAQ:XRAY) last posted its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 9th. The medical instruments supplier reported $0.49 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.50 by $0.01. The firm had revenue of $900.50 million for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $916.55 million. DENTSPLY SIRONA had a return on equity of 7.37% and a net margin of 9.42%. DENTSPLY SIRONA’s quarterly revenue was up 16.6% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period in the prior year, the company posted $0.69 earnings per share.  On average, equities analysts expect that  DENTSPLY SIRONA Inc. will post $2.84 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently disclosed a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Friday, October 13th. Investors of record on Friday, September 29th will be issued a dividend of $0.0875 per share. This represents a $0.35 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 0.56%. The ex-dividend date is Thursday, September 28th. DENTSPLY SIRONA’s dividend payout ratio  is currently 22.58%. 
